{
    "id": "degree-of-comparison-hi",
    "title": "Degree of Comparison (तुलना)",
    "description": "विशेषण (Adjective) या क्रियाविशेषण (Adverb) द्वारा गुण, क्रिया या तरीके की तुलना दर्शाने के लिए Degree of Comparison का उपयोग होता है।",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "📚 Introduction (परिचय)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "जब दो या दो से अधिक व्यक्तियों, वस्तुओं या स्थानों के गुण, मात्रा या क्रिया की तुलना की जाती है, तो उसे <b>Degree of Comparison</b> कहते हैं।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "🔄 3 Degrees Overview",
                        "headers": ["Degree", "हिंदी में", "Definition", "Example"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>Positive</b>", "समानता", "No comparison or Equal comparison (समान है)", "He is <b>as tall as</b> Ram."],
                            ["<b>Comparative</b>", "अधिकता", "Compare 2 things (एक दूसरे से बेहतर)", "He is <b>taller than</b> Ram."],
                            ["<b>Superlative</b>", "श्रेष्ठता", "Compare 2+ things (सबसे श्रेष्ठ)", "He is the <b>tallest</b> boy in class."]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "1️⃣ Formation Rules (रूप बनाने के नियम)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Regular Adjectives",
                        "headers": ["Type", "Rule", "Positive", "Comparative (-er)", "Superlative (-est)"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["Short Words", "+er / +est", "tall", "taller", "tallest"],
                            ["Ends in 'e'", "+r / +st", "large", "larger", "largest"],
                            ["Ends in 'y'", "y → i + er/est", "happy", "happier", "happiest"],
                            ["CVC (Big)", "Double last letter", "big", "bigger", "biggest"],
                            ["Long Words", "more / most", "beautiful", "more beautiful", "most beautiful"]
