                        "rows": [
                            ["good / well", "better", "best"],
                            ["bad / ill", "worse", "worst"],
                            ["little", "less", "least"],
                            ["much / many", "more", "most"],
                            ["far", "farther", "farthest"],
                            ["old", "older / elder", "oldest / eldest"]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "2️⃣ Key Rules: 'The' and 'Than'",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "rules_table_section",
                    "content": {
                        "headers": ["Degree", "Keyword", "Rule"],
                        "rows": [
                            {
                                "Degree": "Comparative",
                                "Keyword": "than",
                                "Rule": "Comparative form के बाद हमेशा <b>than</b> आता है।<br>Example: Better <b>than</b>, Taller <b>than</b>"
                            },
                            {
                                "Degree": "Superlative",
                                "Keyword": "the",
                                "Rule": "Superlative form से पहले हमेशा <b>the</b> आता है।<br>Example: <b>The</b> best, <b>The</b> tallest"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "3️⃣ Sentence Transformation (वाक्य परिवर्तन)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "एक Degree से दूसरी Degree में वाक्य बदलते समय अर्थ नहीं बदलना चाहिए।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Type 1: Comparison between 2 (दो के बीच तुलना)",
                        "headers": ["From", "To", "Example"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>Positive</b>", "<b>Comparative</b>", "Ram is <b>as tall as</b> Shyam.<br>↓<br>Shyam is <b>not taller than</b> Ram."],
                            ["<b>Comparative</b>", "<b>Positive</b>", "Tea is <b>better than</b> coffee.<br>↓<br>Coffee is <b>not as good as</b> tea."]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "note",
                    "content": "<b>Rule:</b> जब केवल दो व्यक्तियों/वस्तुओं की तुलना हो, तो <b>Superlative Degree नहीं बनती</b>।<br>सकारात्मक का नकारात्मक और नकारात्मक का सकारात्मक होता है।"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "4️⃣ Superlative Transformation Patterns",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "जब समूह के साथ तुलना हो, तो तीनों Degrees संभव हैं।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Pattern A: 'The Best' (सबसे श्रेष्ठ)",
                        "headers": ["Degree", "Keyword", "Structure", "Example"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>Superlative</b>", "the ...est", "Subject + the adj-est", "Ganga is <b>the longest</b> river."],
                            ["<b>Comparative</b>", "than any other", "adj-er + than any other", "Ganga is <b>longer than any other</b> river."],
                            ["<b>Positive</b>", "No other", "No other... as adj as", "<b>No other</b> river is <b>as long as</b> Ganga."]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Pattern B: 'One of the Best' (श्रेष्ठों में से एक)",
                        "headers": ["Degree", "Keyword", "Structure", "Example"],
                        "rows": [
                            ["<b>Superlative</b>", "one of the", "one of the adj-est", "Ashoka was <b>one of the greatest</b> kings."],
                            ["<b>Comparative</b>", "than most other", "adj-er + than most other", "Ashoka was <b>greater than most other</b> kings."],
                            ["<b>Positive</b>", "Very few", "Very few... as adj as", "<b>Very few</b> kings were <b>as great as</b> Ashoka."]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "⚠️ Confusion Points (भ्रामक मुद्दे)",
            "content": [
